cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI 

This paper proposes a gradient compression algorithm for federated learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the communication efficiency of the proposed algorithm, which suggests that it may belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Additionally, the paper uses experiments on image classification datasets, which may indicate that it belongs to cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper discusses the convergence of the proposed algorithm, which suggests that it may belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
